About the job
Hey you! Are you looking to make an impact in one of the fastest-growing scale-ups in the FinTech/RegTech industry? Keep reading!

At Fourthline, our mission is to fight financial crime. We help protect the global financial system by verifying millions of identities for banks, neobanks, online brokers, crypto exchanges, and insurers such as N26, Trade Republic, flatexDEGIRO, Nationale Nederlanden, Qonto, Shine, Solarisbank, and more.

Since our journey began in January 2018, we’ve grown to around 250 employees across our Amsterdam and Barcelona offices, representing over 50 nationalities—and we’re just getting started!

About the Team
The Financial Planning & Analysis (FP&A) team works closely with the CFO and is responsible for driving the company’s business planning. Our mission is to provide data-driven financial insights to support key business decisions. As part of the FP&A team, we work cross-functionally with departments including Product, Sales, Marketing, Operations, and HR to ensure well-informed strategic planning.

About the Role
As a Financial Analyst, you will own the financial planning and reporting processes within the Finance team. You’ll translate strategies from various departments into solid financial plans and provide monthly reports to the board, comparing actual performance against key company KPIs.

What You'll Do
Support short-term and long-term financial planning processes;
Prepare and own the monthly financial reporting process;
Conduct business analysis and in-depth financial reviews as needed;
Drive continuous improvements to financial models, reports, and processes;
Partner with various business departments to bring financial insights into decision-making.

What You Bring
Strong communication, engagement, decision-making, problem-solving, and conflict management skills;
A Bachelor’s degree (minimum education requirement);
3 to 5 years of relevant experience, depending on seniority;
Strong financial modeling and analytical skills;
Solid understanding of accounting concepts;
Ability to work effectively in cross-functional teams and a dynamic environment;
Excellent written and verbal English communication skills;
Comfort working in a fast-paced setting;
Advanced Excel skills.

At Fourthline, we believe diversity enriches our culture and inspires you to do your best work. We value your unique talents and perspectives, welcoming them into a safe and inclusive working environment, to ultimately deliver the best products to our customers and society. You're welcome here. Fourthline is for everyone.

Our hiring process is designed to be equal, fair, and transparent. We welcome people from all backgrounds, ethnicities, genders, sexual orientations, ages, abilities, religions, and experiences in life. If you're excited about this role, but your experience does not align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyways. You may just be the right candidate for this or other roles.
